Almost every popular brand of Scotch which you can name is a blend that consists of pure Highland malt whiskey, distilled in pot stills and aged in oak barrels, and then allowed to mingle its heavy, smoky flavors with the lighter essences of Lowland whiskies, also aged. However, there are a few rare unblended Highland malt whiskies which are available at our shop (see below). Many Scotch lovers say that the wondrous peat smoke flavor 1s at its best in a straight malt.
